Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a #pot over medium-low heat. When melted, remove from the heat.

Reserve 3 tsp of @biscuit crumb{125%g} in a #small bowl{} and set aside. Add the remaining biscuit crumb to the butter. Mix together until combined.

Divide between 2 appropriately-sized #glasses{}. Lightly pat the crumbs down with the back of a #spoon to make the base.

Spread the @salted caramel{80%g} over the top of the biscuit base. Pop into the #fridge to firm up.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat and add the @coconut milk{1%pack}.

Bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat and immediately add the @chocolate chips{100%g} and a @salt{pinch}.

Allow to sit for ~{1%minute}, then stir together until the chocolate is melted and everything is well combined. Allow to cool, ~{5%minutes}.

While the mixture cools, roughly bash the @hazelnuts{20%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{} or something heavy.

Pour the cooled coconut chocolate mixture into the glasses.

Cover with #cling film{} and pop into the fridge to set.

> This will take 2-3 hours if you want them fully set, but they'll still be delicious if you want to eat them immediately or after 1 hour.

Before serving, sprinkle each chocolate pot with the reserved biscuit crumb and the hazelnuts.